  "prompt": "Who is the best mobile in 2016?",
  "response": "In 2016, several smartphones stood out as the best in terms of performance, design, and features. Here are some of the top contenders:\n\n### 1. **iPhone 7/7 Plus**\n   - **Key Features:** Water resistance, dual-camera system (on the Plus model), improved performance with the A10 Fusion chip, and the removal of the headphone jack.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Great:** Apple\u2019s iPhone 7 series offered a significant upgrade in terms of camera technology and performance, making it one of the most popular phones of the year.\n\n### 2. **Samsung Galaxy S7/S7 Edge**\n   - **Key Features:** Sleek design, water resistance, excellent AMOLED display, and a fantastic camera.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Great:** The Galaxy S7 Edge, in particular, was praised for its curved display and overall premium feel. It was a strong competitor to the iPhone 7.\n\n### 3. **Google Pixel/Pixel XL**\n   - **Key Features:** Stock Android experience, excellent camera, and fast performance.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Great:** The Google Pixel series marked Google\u2019s first foray into making its own smartphones, and it was widely praised for its camera quality and smooth software experience.\n\n### 4. **OnePlus 3/3T**\n   - **Key Features:** High-end specs at a mid-range price, fast charging, and a clean Android experience.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Great:** The OnePlus 3/3T offered flagship-level performance at a fraction of the cost of other top-tier phones, making it a favorite among tech enthusiasts.\n\n### 5. **LG G5**\n   - **Key Features:** Modular design, dual-camera setup, and a wide-angle lens.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Great:** The LG G5 introduced a unique modular design that allowed users to swap out certain components, though this feature didn\u2019t catch on as much as LG had hoped.\n\n### 6. **HTC 10**\n   - **Key Features:** Premium design, excellent audio quality, and a solid camera.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Great:** The HTC 10 was praised for its build quality and audio performance, making it a strong competitor in the Android space.\n\n### 7. **Sony Xperia XZ**\n   - **Key Features:** Water resistance, high-quality camera, and a sleek design.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Great:** The Xperia XZ offered a great combination of features and design, though it didn\u2019t get as much attention as some of its competitors.\n\n### 8. **Huawei P9**\n   - **Key Features:** Leica-branded dual-camera system, premium design, and good battery life.\n   - **Why It\u2019s Great:** The Huawei P9 was known for its excellent camera, co-developed with Leica, and its overall solid performance.\n\n### **Conclusion:**\nThe \"best\" mobile phone of 2016 depends on your priorities. If you valued **camera quality**, the **Google Pixel** or **iPhone 7 Plus** were excellent choices. For **design and display**, the **Samsung Galaxy S7 Edge** stood out. If you wanted **value for money**, the **OnePlus 3/3T** was hard to beat.\n\nFor most users, the **iPhone 7/7 Plus** and **Samsung Galaxy S7 Edge** were often considered the top overall phones of 2016.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
